# Backend Rules

## Layering

```
Controller → UseCase → Repository → Database
```

- Controllers: HTTP only — validate DTO, call use case, map response
- UseCases: one business scenario per class; orchestration and decisions
- Repositories: all persistence; **Prisma only inside repositories**
- No Prisma / SQL outside repository layer

## Requirements

- Validate all inputs with DTOs (`class-validator` / Zod)
- Centralized error handling (filters / domain errors)
- Structured logging on every use-case entry/exit and failure
- Inject dependencies via NestJS DI; no manual `new` for services
- Keep controllers thin; no business rules in controllers
- Prefer explicit return types on public methods

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — Prisma in controller / use case
await this.prisma.vacancy.create({ data });

// ✅ GOOD — via repository
await this.vacancyRepository.create(data);
```
